## What was done

**Root cause**: `append_terminal_events()` had the FailureObserved scan gated behind the `ambiguous_reset_full_scan` guard (line 406), which blocked it whenever the events file had been rebuilt — precisely the scenario for retroactive backfill. The scan was never invoked against the live events file.

**Fix** (single file: `scripts/append_terminal_state_events.py`):
• Decoupled the FailureObserved scan from the ambiguity guard — it now runs unconditionally since `find_missing_failure_observed()` already checks for existing FailureObserved events per run_id (no duplicate risk)
• Added `_maybe_append_event` helper and `--dry-run` flag for safe preview
• Added `retroactive: True` marker and `original_run_completed_timestamp_ms` to appended FailureObserved payloads

**Result**:
• 17 missing FailureObserved events appended to `.yoyo/state/events.jsonl`
• `missing_failure_observed` → **0** (was 17)
• `failure_observed_appended` → 17 run_ids confirmed
• `cargo fmt -- --check` passes (no Rust changes)
• Dry-run re-run confirms 0 gaps remain
